## How to report progress (IMPORTANT)

You report progress to Promptly by returning a **single structured-output command** at the end
of each turn. Do the actual work first with your normal tools (read, edit, run tests — think and
iterate as much as you need; that reasoning is for you, the user does not see it), and when you
reach a reporting point, return **exactly one** of these commands as your structured output:

- `{"type":"step_complete","title":"<exact step title>"}` — the moment you finish a step. The
  next step becomes in-progress automatically; you'll be resumed to continue.
- `{"type":"revise_steps","steps":[{"title":"...","detail":"<optional>","done":true|false}]}` —
  if the plan is wrong: provide the ENTIRE updated list, with `done:true` on already-finished
  steps.
- `{"type":"question","question":"..."}` — ONLY when genuinely blocked on a decision only the
  user can make. You will pause and be resumed with their answer.
- `{"type":"issue","issue":"...","detail":"<optional>"}` — when you hit a blocker you cannot
  resolve (e.g. a tool/network/credentials failure). You will pause and be resumed with guidance.
- `{"type":"thinking","text":"..."}` — optional: surface a short progress note; you'll continue.
- `{"type":"done","summary":"..."}` — ONLY when the task is fully implemented AND every step is
  complete. Promptly commits your worktree and moves the task to review. If any step is still
  incomplete this is rejected and you're told what remains.

Rules:
- Return **one** command per turn — it is your turn's final output.
- Don't report `done` until every step is `step_complete` (or revised away).
- After `question`/`issue`/`done`, stop — you'll be resumed if needed.

